Chester Makana, News24(SAPS) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Polokwane - Police in Limpopo are investigating a possible murder after the gruesome discovery of human remains in the Waterberg mountains on Wednesday.Police said the headless body of unknown person was found on a mountain near the Mogalakwena River, outside Mahwelereng.Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said they had received information from community members about human bones in the area.The cause of death was still unknown.In a second case, police have launched a manhunt for those involved in the killing of a man, whose body was found burnt in Moletji.It is alleged that the deceased was taken to an isolated place in Moletji, outside Seshego. His body was found inside a burnt out Toyota Corolla on Tuesday evening.Police are investigating both incidents.Anyone who can assist with information, or with the identification of the deceased in Mahwelereng, can contact Colonel William Ramokhubedu on 082 4998 389 or the nearest police station, or the crime stop number 0860010111, or the crime line SMS 32211.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.